content: How many elements are in the intersection of the set of all the prime numbers less than 30 and the set of all the odd numbers greater than zero?

content.question: Should this be our final answer to the user?

The intersection of these two sets (prime numbers less than 30 and odd numbers greater than zero) are: 3, 5, 7, 11, 13, 17, 19, 23, 29.
There are 9 elements in this intersection.
